<b>Harri Hursti</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../716/23716.xml">
computer programmer</link> and former <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../234/52234.xml">
CEO</link> of <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../998/1107998.xml">
F-Secure PLC</link></company>
, a software company based in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../696/13696.xml">
Helsinki, Finland</link>.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> He was also <occupation wordnetid="100582388" confidence="0.8">
<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<word wordnetid="106286395" confidence="0.8">
<part wordnetid="113809207" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<neologism wordnetid="106294441" confidence="0.8">
<activity wordnetid="100407535" confidence="0.8">
<language_unit wordnetid="106284225" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../243/3452243.xml">
Chairman of the Board</link></language_unit>
</activity>
</neologism>
</psychological_feature>
</act>
</part>
</word>
</event>
</occupation>
 and co-founder of ROMmon<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref> where he supervised in the development of the world's smallest 2 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../674/442674.xml">
gigabit</link> traffic analysis product.<p>

Hursti is well known for participating in the Black Box Voting<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref> hack studies, along with Dr. Herbert Thompson. The memory card hack demonstrated in Leon County is popularly known as "the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../604/12843604.xml">
Hursti Hack</link>". This hack was part of a series of four voting machine hacking tests organized by the nonprofit election watchdog group Black Box Voting in collaboration with the producers of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../530/4765530.xml">
HBO</link> documentary, <movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../899/7750899.xml">
Hacking Democracy</link></movie>
. The studies proved serious security flaws in the voting systems of <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../628/264628.xml">
Diebold Election Systems</link></company>
.</p>

